##Huang released from prison infected with pneumonia from Han into Beijing, Hubei Beijing Investigation and prosecution of 16 people

The joint investigation team believes that although "Huang mou-ying incident" occurred in Wuhan Women's prison, but the root of the Hubei Provincial Department of Justice and Hubei Provincial Prison Bureau

CAIJING roundup

With only 5 days time, infection of new crown pneumonia of ex-convict Huang mou-ying, how to return to Beijing from Wuhan under layers of blockade? On March 2, the Ministry of Justice, in conjunction with a central joint investigation team made up of the Central Political and Legal Affairs Commission, the Supreme People's Procuratorate and the Ministry of Public Security, released the results of its investigation into the incident, it is believed that "the incident of Huang mou-ying" is a serious incident caused by dereliction of duty, which brings great hidden danger to the prevention and control of epidemic situation in the capital.

According to a report in the People's Daily, nine people, including party secretary and Director of the Provincial Department of Justice, who bear the main responsibility for leadership, were placed on file for review and investigation after being studied by the Hubei Provincial Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision and reported to the provincial Party Committee for approval.

At the press conference on the prevention and control of the new type of pneumonia in Beijing, the relevant head of the Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision of the Beijing Municipal Commission of Discipline Inspection said that during Huang's visit to Beijing, there were omissions at the Beijing Inspection Station, in residential properties, and at the Municipal Center for Disease Control, and decide on the appropriate penalty. The Beijing Municipal Public Security Bureau is conducting an investigation into whether Huang was involved in any illegal or criminal activities, officials said.

According to public reports, a joint investigation team, approved by the Central Political and Legal Affairs Commission and led by the Ministry of Justice, together with the Central Political and Legal Affairs Commission, the Supreme People's Procuratorate and the Ministry of Public Security, arrived in Hubei on February 27, in close cooperation with the investigation team of Hubei Province, the case of Huang mou-ying who was released from Wuhan Women's prison infected with new crown pneumonia and left for Beijing was investigated.

CCTV related reports said that after the joint investigation team arrived in Hubei, it immediately carried out the investigation and verification work in strict accordance with the law and discipline, connected with the Hubei Provincial Party Committee, the Provincial Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision, and held individual talks with the responsible comrades of the Hubei Provincial Department of Justice and the prison bureau, in-depth investigation of the Wuhan Women's prison and the relevant checkpoints in the Wuhan urban area, collect information, consolidate evidence, find out the Huang mou-ying incident.

The joint investigation team believes that in the case of Huang, the Hubei Provincial Department of Justice is responsible for the leadership, the provincial prison bureau is mainly responsible, the Wuhan Women's prison is directly responsible, and the public security sub-bureau in the east-west Lake District of Wuhan failed to fulfill its duty of investigation and control, relevant personnel should be investigated seriously in accordance with the law and discipline. According to the CCTV report, the joint investigation team transferred the problems found in the investigation to the relevant parties in Hubei Province to deal with them in accordance with the law and discipline, and put forward preliminary recommendations for handling.

The Department of Justice of Hubei Province is weak in leadership and weak in political consciousness and responsibility consciousness. Understanding of the decision-making and deployment of the Party Central Committee is not deep, and the management of the provincial prison bureau is just a formality. Failing to strictly examine and check the documents issued by the Provincial Prison Bureau and submitting them to the political and Legal Committee of the provincial Party Committee for examination and approval, and still failing to correct the errors of the provincial prison bureau in a timely manner after the relevant leaders of the provincial Party Committee gave clear instructions, as a result, there are serious problems in the implementation of the prison system policy in Hubei Province, which runs counter to the prevention and control measures of the epidemic in Hubei Province and even the whole country.

As a result, the administration of Hubei Prison Bureau is not effective, and the consciousness of politics, general situation and rule of law are seriously lacking. There is no overall concept of the Party Central Committee's decision-making and deployment, the prevention and control measures of the Hubei Provincial Party Committee and Provincial Government, and the explicit requirements of the Ministry of Justice. There is no conscious effort to bring prison epidemic prevention into the overall national epidemic prevention work, ignored the Hubei Provincial Party Committee Related Leadership Instruction Request and the Ministry of Justice's explicit stipulation, causes the superior related work request not to carry out.

As a result, the women's prison in Wuhan is not working effectively, and its internal management and system execution are in disorder. In Wuhan Women's prison, in the state of knowing that Huang was a close contact of the British family and had abnormal body temperature, the Ministry of Justice did not implement the system of reporting fever for one hour and strictly enforcing 14-day isolation, and still contacted Huang's relatives in Beijing, huang was transported by police vehicles to a highway junction outside the city, causing him to enter Beijing, posing a great risk of the spread of the epidemic in Beijing.

The public security sub-bureau of east and West Lake District in Wuhan is not well controlled, and its working attitude and discipline are not real. Public Security Sub-bureau is responsible for the entrance control of the police education is not enough, not strict, supervision and inspection in place, leading to the police work slack, careless, vehicles and personnel in and out of Wuhan Verification Lax.

The relevant person in charge of the Discipline Inspection and Supervision Commission of the Beijing Municipal Commission of Discipline Inspection also made the corresponding punishment decision to the relevant departments and units at the press conference on March 2.

As a result, Huang entered Beijing successfully, while Yang and Tan returned to Beijing successfully because of the negligence in the inspection work of the epidemic prevention and control, and because the auxiliary police on duty did not work seriously and did not perform their duties properly, jie Liu, the chief of Qixian checkpoint, and Li Yue, the political commissar, are responsible for the leadership; Wang Zhihai, the deputy chief of Qixian checkpoint, is responsible for handling the post, and should take the main responsibility for the leadership Seeking Xian Checkpoint Auxiliary Police Wang Hui work is not serious, not in place, is the smooth entry of Huang Mou Ying Beijing and Yang mou, Qin mou smooth return to Beijing directly responsible. It was decided that the Party Committee of the Public Security Bureau of the city would inform and hold accountable the Party Committee of the Daxing Sub Bureau, Dismiss Wang Zhihai from his post, give Jie Liu demerits, admonish Li Yue, and dismiss Wang Hui in accordance with relevant regulations.

The district office of Chongwenmenwai in the Eastern District of Foshan and Xinyi home community took the territorial responsibility in the epidemic prevention and control work, and urged the property company to rectify the situation. It was decided that the Dongcheng District Party Committee would issue a notice to the Party Work Committee of Chongwenmenmen Street, and give the General Party Branch Secretary of Xinyi Jiayuan community, Zhang Fan, an inner-party warning.

On February 19, the operator of the Beijing CDC still replied that a person from Wuhan could enter Beijing, which was not in accordance with the deployment requirements of the Leading Group for the prevention and control of the new coronavirus pneumonia in Beijing, has had a very negative impact on this event. It was decided that the Party Committee of the Municipal Health Commission should admonish the director of the Office of the Beijing Municipal Center for Disease Control and Prevention, Yu Jianping, and give a warning to the deputy director of the Office of the Beijing Municipal Center for Disease Control and Prevention, Qian Haikun, and instruct the Beijing Municipal Center for Disease Control and Prevention to strengthen rectification and reform, the deployment of the Leading Group for the prevention and control of the new coronavirus epidemic in Beijing will be conveyed to the grass-roots level in time.

As a result of the failure of Foshan New World Property Management Co. , Ltd. to fulfill the unit responsibility according to the "Four-party Responsibility" , Huang entered the community smoothly. Decided to Beijing New World Property Management Co. , Ltd. reported exposure, interviews with the company's main person, while the Dongcheng District government in accordance with the rules and regulations for its punishment.

The lesson of "Huang mou-ying incident" is very profound. On 30 January, the Ministry of Justice issued an urgent notice on the placement of released prisoners, specifying that prisons should inform prisoners of the status of the epidemic and the requirements for epidemic prevention, and that they should do a good job through the judicial bureau of the place of domicile of the prisoners of their families to persuade prisoners to comply with epidemic prevention arrangements; For those who have served their sentences during the period of isolation observation, the prison shall, after the formalities for their release, place them outside the area of supervision for continued isolation observation. But these measures have not been strictly implemented, resulting in release from prison with the virus, seriously affecting the overall situation of epidemic prevention and control.

To this end, the Ministry of Justice has further stringent measures, has sent 28 supervision teams to monitor the implementation of anti-epidemic measures in drug rehabilitation facilities and the placement of released prisoners throughout the country. The leadership of the Ministry inspects the implementation of the work of prevention and control of infectious diseases in local prisons through video dispatch every day. All localities should take this as a warning, firmly implement measures, resolutely plug the loopholes in the prevention and export of infectious diseases outside the prison, and conduct 14-day isolation observation of all prisoners before they are released from prison. For those who have less than 14 days to complete their sentences, after they have completed the formalities for release according to law, the relevant departments of communication and coordination will arrange them to remain in isolation and observation in a specific place until the end of 14 days. For those who have served their sentences in the prisons of Hubei Province, the prisons in the territory of Jining province and the prisons in the territory of Quzhou Province, after handling the release formalities in accordance with the law, the relevant departments shall coordinate to arrange isolation in specific places until the end of the epidemic. For those who have been released from prison in Beijing and have no connection with the place where the prison is located, all of them will be temporarily relocated until the end of the epidemic and strictly prevent the importation of the epidemic into Beijing.

Following is the story of Huang mou-ying's "departure from Han Dynasty to Beijing" incident (according to CCTV news on March 2) 

This year 61-year-old Huang mou-ying, female, Hubei Province, Xuan'en County Tujia Autonomous Prefecture, former Hubei Province Xuanen County Water Resources and Fisheries Bureau deputy director and cashier. On February 18,2014, he was sentenced to 10 years in prison by the Intermediate People's Court of the Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture for corruption, which was commuted twice for a total of 14 months. TERM OF IMPRISONMENT FROM 18 April 2011 to 17 February 2020. Before February 17, new crown pneumonia had broken out in Hubei. Huang's younger brother, who lives in Ensch, Hubei, and daughter, who lives in Beijing, contacted the prison to discuss the release of Huang. They all said that due to traffic control and other reasons, can Not come to Wuhan to pick up Huang. Huang was in close contact with a police officer in the prison where he was serving his sentence who was diagnosed as a new case of pneumonia or a suspected case. On February 17, Huang was released from prison and remained in isolation in Wuhan Women's prison.

The prison took Huang's temperature 13 times between February 17 and the morning of February 21, of which 37.3 °C was recorded twice on February 18 and 19. In the meantime, Huang mou-ying repeatedly find dry police, request to go home. Police officers and his daughter contact, his daughter said to find a solution. After the dry police and her daughter's ex-husband on the morning of February 21, by the prison will be sent to the North Wuhan high-speed Toll Station to pick up its mouth.

On the morning of February 21, officers took Huang, who had been under observation in isolation, to the entrance of the prison to give him a lecture on the relevant epidemic prevention regulations and ask him to write a letter of guarantee for 14 days of home isolation after his release from prison. Officers will take Huang out of the prison, by Hubei Brand Iveco police car to Wuhan North high-speed Toll Plaza, Walk Huang to Kakou. At that time, the same car also had a Xiaogan released from prison Li Mou, also in the toll station to bring back his son Xiaogan, Li Mou and his close contacts a total of four people, all in designated local isolation. Previously, the British family has been with the card mouth police officers on duty to explain the intention, waiting outside the card mouth. At that time, the public security officer of the Cheung Ching Street police station of the east-west Lake district public security sub-bureau in Wuhan failed to carry out the duty of investigating and controlling Huang, and released him.

Huang entered the Beijing–Hong Kong–Macau Expressway at 11:30 on February 21st with his daughter and her ex husband. He arrived in Beijing in the early hours of February 22nd and was diagnosed as new coronary pneumonia on February 24th.
